-- BNP to slash dividend, issue bonds as U.S. settlement nears- WSJ
-- 
-- Fri Jun 27, 2014 07:59AM EDT
-- None



PARIS, June 27 (Reuters) - France's biggest listed bank BNP Paribas plans to slash its dividend and sell billions of euros in bonds to investors next week, as it nears a settlement with U.S. authorities over violations of sanctions, the Wall Street Journal reported on Friday.

BNP Paribas was not immediately available for a comment.